{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "But concerning the times and the seasons, brothers, you have no need that anything be written to you.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "For you yourselves know well that the day of the Lord comes like a thief in the night.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "For when they are saying, {\n"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Peace and safety,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "then sudden destruction will come on them, like birth pains on a pregnant woman. Then they will in no way escape."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "But you, brothers, aren’t in darkness, that the day should overtake you like a thief.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "You are all children of light and children of the day. We don’t belong to the night, nor to darkness,\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "so then let’s not sleep, as the rest do, but let’s watch and be sober.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "For those who sleep, sleep in the night; and those who are drunk are drunk in the night.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "But since we belong to the day, let’s be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love, and for a helmet, the hope of salvation.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "For God didn’t appoint us to wrath, but to the obtaining of salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "who died for us, that, whether we wake or sleep, we should live together with him.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Therefore exhort one another, and build each other up, even as you also do.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "But we beg you, brothers, to know those who labor among you, and are over you in the Lord and admonish you,\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "and to respect and honor them in love for their work’s sake. Be at peace among yourselves.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "We exhort you, brothers: Admonish the disorderly; encourage the faint-hearted; support the weak; be patient toward all.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "See that no one returns evil for evil to anyone, but always follow after that which is good for one another and for all.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Always rejoice.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Pray without ceasing.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "In everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus toward you.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Don’t quench the Spirit.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Don’t despise prophecies.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Test all things, and hold firmly that which is good.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Abstain from every form of evil.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "May the God of peace himself sanctify you completely. May your whole spirit, soul, and body be preserved blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "He who calls you is faithful, who will also do it.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Brothers, pray for us.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "I solemnly command you by the Lord that this letter be read to all the holy brothers.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "letters",
          "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you. Amen."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}